Focus on:
- Decisions that will change how work is done
- Action items with clear owners and deadlines
- Risks that could derail projects
- Themes that appear across multiple meetings
- Information that would be valuable for someone catching up on the week

Ignore:
- Routine status updates without decisions
- Minor administrative details
- Casual conversation or tangential topics